quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  45,1,"Ha, Mim. (The are the names of letter of the Arabic alphabet, and only Allah knows their meaning here)"
  45,2,"The successive sending down of the Book is from Allah, The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Wise"
  45,3,Surely in the heavens and the earth are indeed signs for the believers
  45,4,"And in your creation, and (in every kind of) beast He disseminates are signs for a people who have certitude"
  45,5,"And (in) the differences (Or: alternation) between the night and the daytime, and whatever provision Allah sends down from the heaven, so He gives life therewith to the earth after its death, and the (constant) turning about of the winds, there are signs for a people who consider"
  45,6,"Those are the signs of Allah that We recite to you with the Truth. In which discourse then, after Allah and His signs, (will) they believe"
  45,7,Woe to every constantly vicious (and persistent) falsifier
  45,8,"(Who) hears the signs (i.e. ayat, signs or verses) of Allah recited to him; thereafter he persists in waxing proud, as if he has not heard them; so give him the (good) tidings of a painful torment"
  45,9,"And when he knows anything of Our signs, he takes them to himself in mockery; those will have a degrading torment"
  45,10,"Beyond them (is) Hell; and whatever they have earned will not avail them anything, nor (avail) the ones they take to themselves as constant patrons apart from Allah; and they will have a tremendous torment"
  45,11,This is guidance; and the ones who have disbelieved in the signs of their Lord will have a painful torment of chastisement
  45,12,"Allah is He Who has subjected to you the sea that the ships may run in it at His Command, and that you may seek of His Grace, and that possibly you would thank (Him)"
  45,13,"And He has subjected to you whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth, all together from Him. Surely in that are signs for a people who meditate"